
= About the project =

== What are we working on? ==

First of~all, Luwrain is a~Linux-based specialized OS and a~place to~apply any new ideas  and experience.
Linux grew~up from a~amateurish experiment to~a~serious platform, 
suitable for~creating the~cutting-edge technologies.
Android, Tizen and FirefoxOS nicely proved that it~is really so.
Thinking about their success,
 we'd like to~consider the~current time as~a~very fortunate moment
for~an~attempt to~solve various problems in~area of~assistive technologies.
However, one important thing gives there a~significant  difference between 
our work and the~platforms mentioned above. 
The~usual gadgets, unfortunately, are sometimes considered   as~curious toys, not~more,
while there are no~doubts whether the~devices with~accessible OS are an~irreplaceable tool or an~item just for~entertainment.
They are always the~former as disabled persons are not~able to~do~without them.

We gathered our~project philosophy in~following ten brief statements:

# It is an OS completely designed for the~blind and visually impaired persons
# It must be convenient, fast and clearly understandable
# It~has~to support various languages and localizations
# It aims to be~sutable for~desktop computers as~well~as for mobile devices
# It is~based on~the~Linux kernel and other FOSS software
# No bias towards any particular  hardware type
# It~is a~non-profitable project
# Its auditory is all users who need it;
no~matter what experience  they got, 
what country are they from,
what profession are they occupied~in and so~on
# Everybody is~able to~participate in~its development,
but authors urge everybody to~respect the~accepted quality requirements for~all incoming patches
# We believe available experience in~GNU/Linux world is~enough at~least to~start this work

